TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(1,4,1);
$b1 = random(2,5,1);
$x1 = random(1,5,1);
$y1 = sqrt($a1 + $b1*$x1);
$m1 = $b1/(2*($a1+$b1*$x1)**.5);

BEGIN_TEXT
If \( f(x) =  \sqrt { $a1 + $b1 x }  \), find \( f'( $x1 ) \), using the
definition of derivative. \( f'( $x1 ) \) is the limit as \(x\to\) \{ans_rule()\}
of the expression
$BR
\{ans_rule(40)\}
$BR
The value of this limit is
\{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = $x1;
$ans2 = "(sqrt($a1 + $b1*x) - $y1)/(x - $x1)";
$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(fun_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans));


